<h1>PI: popfragment</h1>
<p>
  The purpose is to import a fragment defined in the script, 
  and make this expandable on mouseover.
</p>
<pre class="piline">
&lt;?_wxt popfragment id="" ?&gt;
</pre>

<p>The parameters are:</p>
<table cellpadding="10px">
  <tr>
    <td  style="vertical-align:top"><strong>id</strong> (mandatory)</td>
    <td>The id of the fragment we want to pop.
     </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td  style="vertical-align:top"><strong>text</strong> (optional)</td>
    <td>A string that will be shown as clickable. If omitted the <em>id</em> will be shown.
     </td>
  </tr>

  
</table>

<p class="stylefoot">
Styleclass describing this PI is: <em>wxtpopfragment</em>.
See distributed std styles.
</p>

<h2>Examples:</h2>

<pre  class="prettyprint lang-html">
&lt;div&gt;&lt;?_wxt popfragment id="pf2" text="Ronaldhino"?&gt; is a wellknown footballplayer
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>


</body>
